{
  "events": [
    {
      "id": "first_command",
      "tier": "setpiece",
      "weight": 3,
      "repeatable": false,
      "roles": [
        {
          "name": "officer",
          "when": [
            {
              "type": "rank",
              "role": "officer",
              "op": "lt",
              "vsRole": "self"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "when": [
        {
          "type": "rank",
          "role": "self",
          "op": "gte",
          "value": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "skill",
          "role": "self",
          "skill": "tactics",
          "op": "gte",
          "value": 2
        }
      ],
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": "lead_from_front",
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "officer",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": 30
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustStress",
              "role": "self",
              "delta": 8
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 3
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name}'s first command, and {self.name} took the worst of it personally — first into the danger, last out. {officer.name} and the others marked it forever: this is an officer who spends themselves before they spend us. The rank was earned the only way rank is ever truly earned, in the eyes of the people who must obey it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "command_coldly",
          "requires": [
            {
              "type": "trait",
              "role": "self",
              "trait": "Ruthless",
              "kind": "nature",
              "present": true
            }
          ],
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "officer",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": -10
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustStress",
              "role": "officer",
              "delta": 10
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 4
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} spent the command like coin and bought the objective with it. The mission succeeded, brilliantly, at a cost {officer.name} counted in faces. They will follow {self.name} anywhere now — out of respect for the results and fear of being the next line in the ledger. It is a kind of loyalty. The colder kind."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "share_the_glory",
          "requires": [
            {
              "type": "trait",
              "role": "self",
              "trait": "Just",
              "kind": "nature",
              "present": true
            }
          ],
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "officer",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": 25
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustSkill",
              "role": "officer",
              "skill": "tactics",
              "delta": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 2
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} won the action and then, in the report that went up the chain, named {officer.name} and the others before {self.name}'s own part in it. Glory shared is glory multiplied — every name {self.name} lifted is a person who will lift {self.name} in turn, for the rest of a career that has only just begun."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "the_contested_promotion",
      "tier": "setpiece",
      "weight": 3,
      "repeatable": true,
      "roles": [
        {
          "name": "competitor",
          "when": [
            {
              "type": "rank",
              "role": "competitor",
              "op": "gte",
              "vsRole": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "relationship",
              "from": "competitor",
              "to": "self",
              "op": "lte",
              "value": 10
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "when": [
        {
          "type": "rank",
          "role": "self",
          "op": "gte",
          "value": 2
        }
      ],
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": "win_on_merit",
          "cost": {
            "influence": 1
          },
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "setCharFlag",
              "role": "competitor",
              "flag": "passed_over",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "competitor",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": -15
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 3
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "The post went to {self.name} on the record alone — cleaner service, harder results, an argument no board could refuse. {competitor.name} of {competitor.house} was passed over fairly, which is the most galling way to lose. They congratulated {self.name} with a face that promised this was not finished."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "undermine_rival",
          "requires": [
            {
              "type": "trait",
              "role": "self",
              "trait": "Schemer",
              "kind": "aptitude",
              "present": true
            }
          ],
          "cost": {
            "agents": 1
          },
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "setCharFlag",
              "role": "competitor",
              "flag": "feud",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "competitor",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": -35
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} did not win the post so much as ensure {competitor.name} lost it — a doubt planted, a past failure resurfaced at the perfect hour. The promotion is {self.name}'s. So is an enemy who knows exactly what happened and can prove nothing, which is the most dangerous kind to make."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "defer_gracefully",
          "requires": [
            {
              "type": "trait",
              "role": "self",
              "trait": "Honorable",
              "kind": "nature",
              "present": true
            }
          ],
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "competitor",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": 40
            },
            {
              "type": "addBond",
              "from": "self",
              "to": "competitor",
              "bond": "sworn",
              "strength": 50
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} judged {competitor.name} the better fit for this post, this once, and said so to the board. The rank went elsewhere. But {competitor.name} of {competitor.house} learned that {self.name} could be trusted with the truth even when it cost — and there is no promotion in the service worth what that trust will return."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "the_loyalty_test",
      "tier": "setpiece",
      "weight": 3,
      "repeatable": false,
      "roles": [
        {
          "name": "superior",
          "when": [
            {
              "type": "rank",
              "role": "superior",
              "op": "gt",
              "vsRole": "self"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "when": [
        {
          "type": "rank",
          "role": "self",
          "op": "gte",
          "value": 3
        }
      ],
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": "obey",
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "superior",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": 30
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustStress",
              "role": "self",
              "delta": 10
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{superior.name} of {superior.house} gave {self.name} an order that was really a question — about loyalty, about how far {self.name} would go on another's word. {self.name} carried it out. The trust earned is real, and so is the thing {self.name} now knows about themselves, which does not go back in its box."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "refuse_on_principle",
          "requires": [
            {
              "type": "trait",
              "role": "self",
              "trait": "Honorable",
              "kind": "nature",
              "present": true
            }
          ],
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "superior",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": -25
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 3
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustStress",
              "role": "self",
              "delta": 6
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} refused — quietly, respectfully, immovably. {superior.name} lost a useful subordinate and gained a measure of a person who would not be bent, which powerful people both resent and, in their colder calculations, value. The promotion did not come. Something harder to name did."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "obey_then_leak",
          "requires": [
            {
              "type": "trait",
              "role": "self",
              "trait": "Schemer",
              "kind": "aptitude",
              "present": true
            }
          ],
          "cost": {
            "agents": 1
          },
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "setCharFlag",
              "role": "superior",
              "flag": "marked_for_death",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} obeyed {superior.name} to the letter — and kept a copy of everything. The order was carried out; the promotion granted; and somewhere in {self.name}'s keeping now sits the proof of what {superior.name} asked, a knife that need never be drawn to do its work. Loyalty, with an exit."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "the_field_promotion",
      "tier": "situation",
      "weight": 4,
      "repeatable": true,
      "when": [
        {
          "type": "rank",
          "role": "self",
          "op": "gte",
          "value": 2
        },
        {
          "type": "skill",
          "role": "self",
          "skill": "leadership",
          "op": "gte",
          "value": 2
        }
      ],
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": "seize_the_moment",
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustStress",
              "role": "self",
              "delta": 6
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 2
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "The senior officer fell, the line wavered, and {self.name} did not wait for permission to do what permission would have been too slow to grant. By the time the chain of command caught up, {self.name} had already won the thing and worn the rank in all but paper. They made it paper. They had to."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "hold_the_line",
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "adjustSkill",
              "role": "self",
              "skill": "discipline",
              "delta": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} did not seize the empty command; {self.name} held the assigned post flawlessly and let the proper authority sort the rest. No glory, no overreach, no enemies made by stepping over anyone. Some careers are built in leaps. Others, quieter and harder to derail, are built exactly like this."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
