              "delta": 35
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 4
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{admiral.name} of {admiral.house}, who has commanded fleets since before {self.name} could walk, chose {self.name} as the one to carry the doctrine forward. To be named heir to a great commander's thinking is rarer than blood-inheritance and harder to live up to. {self.name} rose to it, and the old admiral, watching, allowed themselves to be proud."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "eclipse_them",
          "requires": [
            {
              "type": "trait",
              "role": "self",
              "trait": "Ambitious",
              "kind": "nature",
              "present": true
            }
          ],
          "effects": [
            {
              "type": "advanceCareer",
              "role": "self"
            },
            {
              "type": "setCharFlag",
              "role": "admiral",
              "flag": "feud",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustRelationship",
              "from": "admiral",
              "to": "self",
              "delta": -20
            },
            {
              "type": "adjustCounter",
              "key": "standing",
              "delta": 5
            },
            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} did not wait to inherit {admiral.name}'s shadow; {self.name} stepped out of it, in public, with a victory the old admiral could not have won and would not soon forgive. The fleet has a new name to follow. The old one watches it rise the way the setting sun watches the dawn — and begins, quietly, to plan."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "the_governors_seat",
      "tier": "setpiece",
      "weight": 3,
      "repeatable": false,
      "when": [
