              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name}'s first case, and {self.name} ruled as the law demanded rather than as power preferred — even when {defendant.name} of {defendant.house} had friends who expected otherwise. A reputation for incorruptible judgment is the slowest to build and the only one a magistrate cannot survive without. {self.name} began to build it here."
